                Employment
   Opportunities

   You may apply online for any of the listed openings simply by following
   the "Apply online now for this job" link after each listing. The online
   employment application system is easy and convenient to use. Assigning
   you a user I.D. and password allows you to complete your application in
   steps while saving the information you have completed to date. You may
   refer back to a previous application to complete it or update it for a
   new vacancy. If you have already begun an application online and need
   to complete it for submission, just use the "Apply online now for this
   job" link, then login

   Current Openings for the City of Flagstaff:
     __________________________________________________________________

   Plant Operator/Wastewater Treatment
   $12.62 to $15.02 DOE
   Application must be submitted by February 22, 2002
   shift work
   Vacancy #005-02

   Performs specialized technical work relating to the proper operations
   and maintenance of the City's wastewater treatment plant. This includes
   collecting and testing wastewater samples, recording data, adjusting
   equipment and routine maintenance as assigned. Includes weekend and
   on-call hours.

   HOURS 7:00am to 3:30pm or 8:00am to 4:30pm (dependant on shift
   assignment)

   Full-time, Tenure-eligible

   MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS High School diploma or GED; Must possess, or
   obtain within two years of employment, a Grade 2 certificate in
   wastewater treatment; Must live, or relocate within three months of
   employment, within a 15 mile radius of downtown Flagstaff; Must possess
   a valid AZ driver's license; Must posses a telephone for on-call
   status; Operations, maintenance, or laboratory experience in a
   wastwater plant or related experience (i.e. mechanical, electrical or
   construction).

   DESIRED EXPERIENCE Related coursework in Chemistry, Biology, or
   Environmental Science; Some mechanical aptitude and ability to analyze
   and troubleshoot.

